Privacy Policy for Medico

Effective Date: 27/05/2024

1. Introduction

Welcome to Medico, a hospital receptionist app designed to manage doctor appointment bookings and send confirmation messages. This Privacy Policy outlines how [Your Company Name] ("we", "our", or "us") collects, uses, discloses, and protects your information.

2. Information We Collect

Personal Information: We collect personal information such as names, phone numbers, and email addresses when you book an appointment.
Doctor Information: Details of doctors including their names, specialties, and availability are collected to facilitate bookings.
Usage Data: We collect information on how you interact with our app to improve our services.
3. How We Use Your Information

Appointment Booking: To schedule and manage doctor appointments.
Communication: To send confirmation messages and important updates regarding your appointments. This includes sending SMS messages to the phone numbers provided by patients.
Improvement: To analyze usage data and enhance our appâ€™s functionality and user experience.
4. Permissions We Request

SMS Permission:
Our app requests permission to send SMS messages to confirm appointments and provide updates. This is essential for ensuring that patients receive timely notifications about their appointments. We do not use this permission for any other purpose, and we do not share this information with third parties.

Internet Permission:
Our app requests Internet access to communicate with our servers for appointment booking and retrieving doctor information.

5. Information Sharing and Disclosure

We do not share your personal information with third parties except:

With your consent: We will share information with companies, organizations, or individuals outside of Medico when we have your consent to do so.
For legal reasons: We will share information if we believe that access, use, preservation, or disclosure of the information is reasonably necessary to:
Comply with applicable laws, regulations, legal processes, or enforceable governmental requests.
Protect against harm to the rights, property, or safety of Medico, our users, or the public as required or permitted by law.
6. Data Security

We use appropriate security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, please be aware that no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure.

7. Data Retention and Deletion

We retain your personal data only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy or as required by law. You may request deletion of your personal data at any time, and we will comply with your request in accordance with applicable laws.

8. Your Data Protection Rights

Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:

Access: You have the right to request copies of your personal data.
Rectification: You have the right to request that we correct any information you believe is inaccurate or incomplete.
Erasure: You have the right to request that we erase your personal data, under certain conditions.
Restriction of Processing: You have the right to request that we restrict the processing of your personal data, under certain conditions.
Objection to Processing: You have the right to object to our processing of your personal data, under certain conditions.
Data Portability: You have the right to request that we transfer the data that we have collected to another organization, or directly to you, under certain conditions.
9. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

